This is my variation of the famous Drexel Strategy. I've modified a few of the things, for instance using a JMA smoothing average as well as the RSX calculation from LazyBear. This strategy does not repaint I do not think, when I called the high and low I used [1] or calculated things from open. I believe I avoided curve fitting because I get similar results across most pairs. This works best on the 1hr and below time frames. Hope you get lots of use out of it.
